OL,3,CDerby's market hall reopens after
OL,4,Cseven-year multi-million pound
OL,5,Crenovation
OL,7,FThe Market Hall was officially
OL,8,Fdeclared open on 29 May, 1866 by Mayor
OL,9,FFrederick Longdon, where the occasion
OL,10,Fwas marked with an appropriate
OL,11,Finaugural ceremony, including a
OL,12,Fperformance of Handel's Messiah.
OL,14,FThe council said the transformed
OL,15,FMarket Hall will bring together the
OL,16,Fbest of the region's independent
OL,17,Fshopping, eating, drinking, and
OL,18,Fentertainment, and will offer a
OL,19,Fvariety of new features and
OL,20,Fexperiences for visitors, such as:
